This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 25 development cycle. Changing version to '25'.

I do not see any crash during opening anymore. I "played" with calendar now and I didn't crash it during my tests: 1) Repeated opening and closure of this app 2) Quick menu opening, clicking among different settings
I tested this in gnome-calendar-3.22.1-1.fc26.x86_64
and
gnome-calendar-3.20.4-1.fc24.x86_64
I propose to close this bug.
